org.linqs.psl.model.rule.arithmetic

Class WeightedGroundArithmeticRule

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.linqs.psl.model.rule.arithmetic.AbstractGroundArithmeticRule
      • org.linqs.psl.model.rule.arithmetic.WeightedGroundArithmeticRule
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    GroundRule, WeightedGroundRule

    public class WeightedGroundArithmeticRule
extends AbstractGroundArithmeticRule
implements WeightedGroundRule
    An AbstractGroundArithmeticRule that is weighted, i.e., it corresponds to a weighted hinge-loss potential that measures the compatibility of GroundAtom values.
    Author:
    Stephen Bach

      • getWeight

        public Weight getWeight()
        Description copied from interface: WeightedGroundRule
        Returns the Weight of this WeightedGroundRule.

        Until WeightedGroundRule.setWeight(Weight) is called, this GroundRule's weight is the current weight of its parent Rule. After it is called, it remains the most recent Weight set by WeightedGroundRule.setWeight(Weight).

        Specified by:
